parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Head Gasket Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine overheats
the temperature gauge rises
the engine makes a knocking or grinding noise
the oil level drops suddenly
the check engine light comes on
the engine loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Oil Leaks or Low Oil Pressure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine due to oil leaks or low oil pressure can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine makes a rattling or clunking noise
the oil level drops suddenly
the check engine light comes on
the engine loses power or stalls
the engine overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Warning Lights or Indicators
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of warning lights or indicators can prevent the driver from taking corrective action, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: No warning lights or indicators come on prior to engine failure
the check engine light comes on only after the engine has failed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress in Rear Brake Light Housing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water accumulation in the rear brake light housing can cause corrosion, leading to inoperative brake lights, which can lead to accidents or confusion for other drivers.

corrosion of the brake light bulb socket.
